CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Higher Education – Nonresident Tuition Student Financial Assistance –
3 Exemption for Dependents of State or Local Public Safety Employees
4 (Maryland Fallen Heroes Tuition Benefits Act)
5 FOR the purpose of exempting spouses and financially dependent children of certain State
6 or local public safety employees from paying out–of–state or out–of–county tuition at
7 a public institution of higher education in the State; altering the method for
8 allocating funds for the Edward T. and Mary A. Conroy Memorial Scholarship
9 Program and the Jean B. Cryor Memorial Scholarship Program; and generally
10 relating to nonresident tuition exemptions for student financial assistance for
11 spouses and financially dependent children of State or local public safety employees.
12 BY adding to
13 Article – Education
